	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="UK11_DA_dig.cite">
  <title>dig:cite <lnpid>id-UK11DA-29418</lnpid></title>
  <body>
    <section>
      <p><sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml> becomes
          <targetxml>abstract:head/ref:citations/ref:cite4thisresource</targetxml>.</p></section>
    <section><p><b>Exceptional use case, <sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml> with pcdata:</b> Generally
          <sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml> contains <sourcexml>ci:cite</sourcexml> which transforms
        to <targetxml>lnci:cite</targetxml> per General Markup rules. If child
          <sourcexml>ci:cite</sourcexml> is not present, conversion should create
          <targetxml>lnci:cite/lnci:content</targetxml> to hold the pcdata. See example # 2. Known
        to occur in dpsi 0JUM and 0KVS "smart forms".</p></section>
    <note><targetxml>abstract:head</targetxml> is a required child of
        <targetxml>abstract:abstract</targetxml>. Source <sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml>,
        <sourcexml>leg:dates</sourcexml>, <sourcexml>leg:govoffice</sourcexml>,
        <sourcexml>leg:categories</sourcexml>, and <sourcexml>dig:type</sourcexml> map within
        <targetxml>abstract:head</targetxml>. If none is present, create
        <targetxml>abstract:head</targetxml> as an empty element.</note>

    <pre>
              <b><i>Example: Source XML 1</i></b>
                  

&lt;dig:body&gt;
  &lt;dig:info&gt;
    &lt;dig:cite&gt;
      &lt;ci:cite&gt;
          &lt;ci:content&gt;LNB News 04/05/2012 34&lt;/ci:content&gt;
      &lt;/ci:cite&gt;
    &lt;/dig:cite&gt;
  &lt;/dig:info&gt;
&lt;/dig:body&gt;
 
	</pre>
    <pre>
                    
              <b><i>Example: Target XML 1</i></b>
    
&lt;abstract:head&gt;
  &lt;ref:citations&gt;
    &lt;ref:cite4thisresource&gt;
      &lt;lnci:cite&gt;
         &lt;lnci:content&gt;LNB News 04/05/2012 34&lt;/lnci:content&gt;
      &lt;/lnci:cite&gt;
    &lt;/ref:cite4thisresource&gt;
  &lt;/ref:citations&gt;
&lt;/abstract:head&gt;

                </pre>
    <pre>
              <b><i>Example: Source XML 2, <sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml> with pcdata</i></b>
                  

&lt;dig:body&gt;
  &lt;dig:info&gt;
    &lt;dig:cite&gt;CON 29 M&lt;/dig:cite&gt;
  &lt;/dig:info&gt;
&lt;/dig:body&gt;
 
	</pre>
    <pre>
                    
              <b><i>Example: Target XML 2, <sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml> with pcdata</i></b>
    
